author: Justin Barry
title: Warren Sapp embraces coaching under Deion Sanders revealing unexpected passion and strong commitment after years of resistance to the game
text:
Early Reluctance Transformed
Warren Sapp, whose initial stance was one of clear disinterest, now finds himself fully captivated by coaching. Despite his earlier reservations about stepping into this new role, he has discovered a genuine passion that has reshaped his view on being involved in the game off the field.
A New Chapter Under Inspiring Leadership
Working closely with a dynamic mentor has been pivotal in igniting this unexpected enthusiasm. The transformation in his attitude reflects a broader trend among respected athletes who, after lengthy careers, unearth fresh opportunities to influence the sport. His candid admission of growing addiction to coaching echoes a deeper connection, one that surpasses the traditional allure of competitive play.
Redefining His Legacy
Sappâ€™s evolution from reluctant veteran to an engaged mentor exemplifies how change can emerge even when it seems least likely. His journey under a charismatic leader illustrates the power of embracing innovative paths, challenging long-held beliefs, and reinventing oneself within a familiar arena. This personal metamorphosis has reinforced his commitment to shaping the next generation of talent, marking a significant milestone in his illustrious career.

title: The digital currency platform Enet Crypto Center Limited successfully obtained the U.S. Fincen MSB license, legalizing and regularizing transactions. | News | decaturdailydemocrat.com
text: On December 20th, after submitting proof of MSB registration completion, Enet Crypto Center Limited (hereinafter referred to as Enet) officially obtained the U.S. Fincen MSB license on November 15. This marks a further step in Enet's compliance journey, allowing it to legally conduct currency exchange business in the United States, further expanding its international development space. This establishes a solid foundation for serving global users and enables Enet to provide users with safer, compliant, efficient, and convenient digital economic transaction services Since 2018, the U.S. Department of Treasury and the Securities and Exchange Commission have repeatedly emphasized that MSBs (Money Services Businesses) include virtual currency exchanges and their managers. The regulated entities are businesses and companies related to financial services. The regulatory scope includes international remittances, foreign exchange, currency trading, ICO issuance, and management of prepaid projects. Operating digital asset-related business within the United States requires a license. Hence, Enetâ€™s possession of the license grants it legal status in the U.S., distinguishing it from other irregular platforms. Enet Exchange has always sought higher-level and broader development. As a global leader in decentralized exchanges, it is committed to breaking national boundaries and achieving global integration. Based on Enet's public blockchain technology, it aims to realize scenario implementations in various fields, including capital, digital asset management, digital asset payment, blockchain charity, blockchain gaming, blockchain entertainment, blockchain shopping, and blockchain community games, thereby creating a complete decentralized digital asset ecosystem. Holding a license is of great significance for current exchanges. Obtaining official permission from the respective countries reflects the strength and credibility of the exchange. For most exchanges, a license also acts as a natural barrier for selection. For users, Enet's compliant operation under regulatory conditions is a major advantage, meaning their investments will receive legal protection. Under official permission, Enet strictly meets local regulatory requirements and user protection regulations. Enet will continue to advance its compliance and globalization development, providing safe and convenient digital asset transaction services to more global users. It also calls on other platforms to join the regular development path, contributing to the industry's progress and hoping to achieve industry compliance consensus. author: kake.com
title: Southeast is lashed by more severe weather after deadly storms and tornadoes hit Tennessee - KAKE
text:
By Mary Gilbert and Dalia Faheid, CNN
(CNN) â€” Violent storms were tracking through parts of the South Thursday, a day after deadly, destructive thunderstorms and tornadoes tore through the central and southern US, marking more chaotic weather amid a two-week streak of danger.
Large hail â€“ some the size of golf and tennis balls â€“ pounded parts of the South Thursday, especially in Texas, according to the Storm Prediction Center . Strong winds also were reported from east Texas to South Carolina, leaving numerous reports of downed trees across the region, the prediction center said.
The South still was dealing with substantial damage wrought by storms Wednesday. Tennessee was especially hard hit that day, with multiple tornadoes and water rescues amid flash flood emergencies in the state.
At least one tornado has been reported in the US every day since April 25 â€“ a streak of 15 days and counting - and there have been more than 300 reported tornadoes during that span. April and May are the most active months for tornadoes and severe weather, and that reputation continued Thursday, when more than 60 million people in the South and East were at risk of severe thunderstorms and tornadoes.
A tornado emergency unfolded Wednesday evening in Maury County, located about 25 miles south of Nashville. The National Weather Service warned of a â€œconfirmed large and destructive tornadoâ€ near the city of Spring Hill. The tornado killed one person and injured about a dozen others, according to county officials.
In northern Alabama, a â€œlarge and destructive tornadoâ€ prompted a tornado emergency in the area of Henagar, a city of a couple thousand people roughly 55 miles east of Huntsville, the National Weather Service said. Itâ€™s still unclear what, if any, damage the tornado caused in the area.
Hereâ€™s the latest on ongoing storms and destruction in the central and southern US:
At least three dead in the South: One person was killed on Wednesday in Claiborne County, Tennessee, when a tree fell on their car amid intense storms, the countyâ€™s emergency management office said. Another person died in Tennessee after a tornado touched down in Maury County Wednesday evening. In North Carolina, one person was killed in Gaston County near Charlotte when a tree fell on their vehicle, officials said.
Tornado injures several, causes significant damage: About a dozen people were injured by the tornado in Maury County, Tennessee, officials confirmed in a press conference Thursday. At least one person is in serious condition, Maury Regional Medical Center spokesperson Rita Thompson told CNN. Video from the scene showed buildings torn to shreds, homes missing large sections of roofs and walls and large trees snapped in half.
Water rescues amid flash flood emergencies: Up to 9 inches of rain triggered flash flood emergencies and water rescues in communities just north of Nashville, Tennessee, Wednesday evening. Flooding in Robertson County blocked roadways and forced water rescues, the countyâ€™s emergency management agency told CNN. Emergency crews have also responded to water rescue calls and evacuated flooded homes in Sumner County, the countyâ€™s emergency management director Ken Weidner said. Sumner County Schools are closed Thursday due to the flooding.

author: @Dailyhuntapp
title: Dave Myers' widow Liliana pays tribute to her 'wonderful, brave' husband
text:
Dave Myers' widow Liliana has paid tribute to her "wonderful, brave" husband.The TV cook, best known as one half of the Hairy Bikers, died at the age of 66, according to a statement on Thursday from his co-star Si King on social media.
King, who was a apart of the motorcycle-riding cooking duo, said Myers had "been fighting cancer for the past couple of years".
In a Facebook post, Myers' widow Liliana said: "Rest in peace, my love.
"My wonderful, brave man. Till next time we meet!"
On The One Show, TV chef Matt Tebbutt, who starred alongside Myers on Saturday Kitchen, described his co-star as a "genuinely lovely guy".
He told presenters Alex Jones and Roman Kemp: "He was very down to earth.
"He was a genuinely lovely guy. Very funny, kind hearted, very warm, engaging."
"And also, which is a very rare thing, he was the same on screen as he was off screen", he added.
"And as we know, in this industry, that's not always the case.
"But Dave was very, very much like that, and to have him around, it kind of made the world brighter and a personality like that, it makes the days go quicker."
Myers' Strictly Come Dancing professional dance partner Karen Hauer, who performed alongside the Hairy Biker on the show's 11th series, also paid tribute.
The 41-year-old said: "Rest well my dear friend. I'm going to miss you so much."
Countdown star Rachel Riley, who also appeared on series 11 of Strictly, remembered Myers as a "great bloke" and posted a selection of photos to social media of the late TV star dancing.
Just heard the terribly sad news about the lovely Hairy Dave Myers.
We were in the Strictly class of 2013 together and Dave, Lili and Iza always brought absolute joy to the green room after every show.
A particularly fond memory was Dave, @ashoztd Nicky Butt and me,â€¦ pic.twitter.com/DexDiTppLO
â€” Rachel Riley MBE ðŸ’™ (@RachelRileyRR) February 29, 2024 \n\n
She said: "Just heard the terribly sad news about the lovely Hairy Dave Myers.
"We were in the Strictly class of 2013 together and Daveâ€¦ always brought absolute joy to the green room after every show.
"A particularly fond memory was Dave, @ashoztd, Nicky Butt and me, gatecrashing an office Christmas party that happened to be in the same hotel we were staying before the show's series final.
"Terrible photo below, we couldn't dance but that didn't stop us! Also, filming Countdown, makeup ladies from far and wide would come and seek him out from their time together as makeup artists.
"He was so universally loved and popular. Huge love to Lili and the family, Dave was a great bloke who will be missed by many."
Former Countdown star Carol Vorderman also paid tribute and said: "I only met Dave once and he was so full of love for the world."
Elsewhere, Great British Bake Off judge Paul Hollywood said he was "gutted" to hear about Myers' death, adding: "This is terrible news! Love to all mate xx."
TV chef James Martin said he was "lost for words", describing Myers as "a very special man".
TV cook Andi Oliver said she was "so sad" to hear that Myers had died and that her "heart goes out" to his family and his co-star King.
Presenter and stylist Gok Wan described it as a "terrible and heartbreaking loss" as he also sent his support to Myers' loved ones.
"Dave made cooking a truly joyful adventure and he shared that joy with millions. The public loved him and his unique partnership with Si. Together they made every viewer feel like a friend."
Chief Content Officer Charlotte Moore pays tribute to Dave Myers -â€¦ pic.twitter.com/4HguGHrd3G
â€” BBC Press Office (@bbcpress) February 29, 2024 \n\n
Radio presenter Bob Harris said he was "very sad to hear this news" while singer Alfie Boe sent his "love and sympathy" to Myers' family and friends.
Across his career, Myers co-presented a host of cooking-travelogue shows and specials for the BBC alongside his friend King.
BBC chief content officer Charlotte Moore said that everyone at the BBC was "incredibly sad" to hear the news of his death.
"Dave made cooking a truly joyful adventure and he shared that joy with millions," she added.
The official BBC Food account also hailed Myers as a "wonderful man and a very talented chef" as they paid tribute.
Elsewhere, the official Strictly Come Dancing social media account called Myers a "true gentleman".
The Hairy Bikers' publishers Orion Books remembered Myers as "brilliantly inspiring and kind".
Myers, born in Barrow-in-Furness, Cumbria, first announced he was receiving treatment for cancer in May 2022, but did not specify what type he had been diagnosed with.
He had started his working life as a make-up artist and first met his co-star and friend King in 1995 while working on a TV drama called The Gambling Man.
Their first TV appearance together was The Hairy Bikers' Cookbook in 2004, which was part cooking show and part travel programme and in the first episode the duo rode the length of Portugal.
Subsequent shows included The Hairy Bikers Ride Again, The Hairy Bikers' Food Tour Of Britain, The Hairy Bikers: Mums Know Best, The Hairy Bikers' Cook Off and Hairy Bikers: Best Of British.
